        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "MiMo: import cookies from Safari, Firefox, and Edge (not Chrome-only)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nCloses #1304 — **MiMo Auto import was Chrome-only on main**; this PR adds the browsers the issue explicitly requested.\n\n### MiMo (#1304)\n\n**Before (`origin/main`):** Auto import only probed Chrome / Chrome Beta / Chrome Canary.\n\n**After (`bf213ac5`):** curated Auto order:\n\n```swift\n[.safari, .chrome, .chromeBeta, .chromeCanary, .firefox, .edge]\n```\n\n- **Safari** — macOS default browser; no Chromium Keychain prompt\n- **Chrome variants** — preserved from main\n- **Firefox / Edge** — added per issue #1304 (“Please support Safari, Firefox, Edge”)\n- **Arc / Brave / other forks** — still **Manual** cookie header (not the full SweetCookieKit default order)\n\nSettings copy, locales, and `docs/mimo.md` now describe Safari + Chrome + Firefox + Edge, not “Chrome only”.\n\n### Related Chrome-only copy fixes (same PR)\n\n- **Mistral**: importer no longer defaults to `[.chrome]` only when the descriptor exposes the full order\n- **Command Code / Alibaba Token Plan**: error text uses `browserCookieOrder.loginHint` instead of “sign in in Chrome”\n- **Docs**: `ollama.md`, `alibaba-token-plan.md`, `augment.md`\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Source diff (MiMo Auto browsers)\n\n| Browser | `origin/main` | this PR |\n|---------|---------------|---------|\n| Safari | ❌ | ✅ (first) |\n| Chrome / Beta / Canary | ✅ | ✅ |\n| Firefox | ❌ | ✅ |\n| Edge | ❌ | ✅ |\n| Arc / full default order | ❌ | ❌ (Manual) |\n\n### Tests (`bf213ac5`)\n\n```\nswift test --filter \"BrowserCookieOrderStatusStringTests|MiMoProviderTests\"\n✔ mimo cookie import order supports safari firefox and edge\n✔ mimo web strategy retries imported sessions after decode failure\n✔ Test run with 31 tests in 2 suites passed\nmake check — 0 violations\n```\n\nLive browser cookie import was not run (AGENTS.md — avoids Keychain prompts); behavior is covered by order regression tests + stubbed MiMo web-strategy import tests.\n\n## Intentionally unchanged\n\n- **Grok** / **OpenCode** (non-Go): still Chrome-only by design\n- **Ollama / Abacus**: Chrome-first + fallback; docs only",
